Everybody pokes fun at jarheads as being dumb, but I never knew one who could not spell his own rank correctly. <br><br>
Being a *Sergeant, USMC* takes a little more upstairs than people on the outside realize. These are highly disciplined, highly trained, articulate people. <br><br>
Marines always stick together, never stab each other in the back in public, and it is very uncharacteristic of them to go about anonomously or hit and run with no e-mail address. It is not the mission oriented stand tall USMC style, and you are not promoted to the rank of Sergeant unless you have been in a while and really fit the bill. These guys never, ever hide behind trees! The image of the USMC is what counts and is always on their mind.<br><br>
I have never known any Marine in the Corps in the 60's and 70's to come to the defense of 60's style protestors and communists, no less! They would self destruct at the mere thought of it! 
